This paper deals with learning vector representations of SQL workloads to support a variety of administration tasks and application features. The paper discusses various methods for vector representations of SQL text and optimized query plans and evaluates them on multiple real SQL workloads. The paper also proposes a new embedding strategy specialized for queries based on tree-structured Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) network architectures. Given the focus on database systems and natural language processing, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DB and cs.CL. However, the paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which makes cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
